<SECOND>PM-AP-Horwitz,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Richard Horwitz Named AP's European Photo Network Director</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard Horwitz, an editor and manager in The
Associated Press photo service, has been named the AP's European
network director.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Hal Buell, AP
assistant general manager for newsphotos.
   Horwitz will work with the AP bureaus throughout Europe to manage
the collection and dissemination of the AP's graphics and photo
report on the continent. He will be based in London and will report
to Horst Faas, AP's photo editor for Europe, Africa and the Middle
East.
   Horwitz, 47, served most recently as assistant chief of
bureau-photos in Chicago, where he was responsible for the news
service's report to a 19-state region in the central United States.
   Horwitz joined the AP as a photo editor in New York in 1965. He
also worked in Boston and Washington before being named to the
Chicago post in 1978.
   He is a native of Chicago and holds bachelor's and master's
degrees from Indiana University.
