<HEAD>Thousands Protest University Overcrowding</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thousands of students demonstrated in
several West German cities to protest overcrowding and housing
shortages at the country's universities.
   Police in Munich said 30,000 students took part in protests
Wednesday in the Bavarian city. About 12,000 students demonstrated
in Stuttgart and 10,000 protesters marched through the northern port
city of Hamburg, police said.
   School officials reported student boycotts at several other
universities. There were no reports of incidents.
   Students and many educators have increasingly complained that
West Germany's universities are far too overcrowded and that there
are critical housing shortages for students in many cities.
