<HEAD>15 Die Of Food Poisoning At Funeral Luncheon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 15 people attending a funeral
lunch for an eight-year-old girl died of food poisoning in the
southern city of Hyderabad, news reports said today.
   Police Commissioner T. S. Rao said Wednesday's tragedy occurred
when an unidentified chemical substance mistaken for salt was used
to prepare the customary lunch, the Press Trust of India reported.
   The agency said four of the dead were children.
   About 20 people ate the lunch and most of them started vomiting.
Two died before they could be given medical help and 13 died later
at the hospital. The remaining five were in critical condition, the
news agency said.
   Hyderabad, capital of Andhra Pradesh state, is about 775 miles
south of New Delhi.
