<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--China-Crash     01-19 0138</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--China-Crash,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Overcrowded Bus Hit By Train At Unmanned Crossing, 32 Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A speeding train slammed into a crowded bus at an
unmanned railroad crossing, killing 32 people and injuring 49, a
newspaper said today.
   The Beijing Daily said the accident occurred Wednesday in Nanhui
county of Jilin province in northern China. It said all the
casualties were among the 81 passengers on the bus. Of the injured,
26 were in serious condition.
   Train No. 533, heading from Meihekou to Songlingang, hit the bus
as it crossed an unmanned railroad intersection. The bus was knocked
about 100 feet and the train derailed, the report said.
   Train accidents are not uncommon in China. The most recent
occurred in December, when a passenger train hit a crowded bus,
killing at least 45 people in Liaoning province.
</TEXT>
