<FIRST>r a PM-PollMethod     01-19 0738</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Poll Method,0759</SECOND>
<HEAD>Poll on Bush Contacted 1,162 at Random</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Poll-Bush, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This Media General-Associated Press poll is based
on telephone interviews Jan. 4-12 with 1,162 adults in the
continental United States. The phone numbers were selected randomly
by computer and interviews were conducted with the adult who had the
most recent birthday.
   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample.
The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that if every adult
American were asked the same questions, the results theoretically
would be within 3 points of the poll's results, 19 times out of 20.
The margin of error is larger for subgroups _ 5 points, for example,
for conservatives.
   There are other sources of potential error in polls, including
the wording and order of questions. These are the questions and
responses in this poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100:
   1. Overall, do you have a favorable or unfavorable opinion of
George Bush? Favorable: 59 percent. Unfavorable: 25. Don't know or
No answer: 17.
   2. How would you rate the job George Bush has done since the
election in preparing to take over the presidency _ excellent, good,
only fair or poor? Excellent: 11. Good: 46. Only fair: 28. Poor: 7.
DK-NA: 9.
   3. What's your overall impression of the Cabinet appointments
made by George Bush _ would you rate them as excellent, good, only
fair or poor? Excellent: 8. Good: 45. Only fair: 30. Poor: 5. DK-NA:
13.
   4. Do you think George Bush's Cabinet will be more conservative
than President Reagan's, or less conservative, or about the same?
More: 11. Less: 21. Same: 60. DK-NA: 9.
   5. Did you want George Bush's Cabinet top be more conservative
than it is, or less conservative, or is it about right? More: 23.
Less: 23. Right: 42. DK-NA: 12.
   6. George Bush has nominated two women to Cabinet positions.
Would you have liked him to nominate more women, or fewer women, or
do you think that it doesn't matter? More: 25. Fewer: 2. Doesn't
matter: 70. DK-NA: 3.
   7. George Bush has nominated one black and two Hispanics to
Cabinet positions. Would you have liked him to nominate more
minorities, or fewer minorities, or do you think that it doesn't
matter? More: 22. Fewer: 4. Doesn't matter: 71. DK-NA: 4.
   8. I'm going to read the names of a few people George Bush has
nominated to join his Cabinet. For each, please tell me whether you
have a favorable or unfavorable opinion of that person, or if you
don't know enough about the person yet to have an opinion.
   a. James Baker, nominee for secretary of state. Favorable: 57.
Unfavorable: 7. Don't know: 36.
   b. John Tower, nominee for secretary of defense. Favorable: 35.
Unfavorable: 12. Don't know: 53.
   c. Richard Thornburgh, selected to continue as attorney general.
Favorable: 51. Unfavorable: 7. Don't know: 42.
   d. Nicholas Brady, selected to continue as secretary of the
treasury. Favorable: 43. Unfavorable: 6. Don't know: 51.
   e. Louis Sullivan, nominee for secretary of health and human
services. Favorable: 27. Unfavorable: 4. Don't know: 69.
   f. Jack Kemp, nominee for secretary of housing and urban
development. Favorable: 52. Unfavorable: 10. Don't know: 39.
   g. Elizabeth Dole, nominee for secretary of labor. Favorable: 66.
Unfavorable: 7. Don't know: 28.
   9. Do you think the secretary of health and human services should
support current abortion law, or should he favor more restrictions
on abortion, or fewer restrictions, or shouldn't it matter what his
position is on abortion? Current law: 19. More restrictions: 28.
Fewer restrictions: 13. Shouldn't matter: 27. DK-NA: 13.
   10. Do you have a favorable or unfavorable opinion of John
Sununu, the man George Bush has appointed to be White House chief of
staff, or haven't you heard enough about John Sununu yet to have an
opinion? Favorable: 12. Unfavorable: 5. Don't know: 83.
   11. What kind of a president do you think George Bush will make _
an excellent president, a good one, only a fair one, or a poor one?
Excellent: 13. Good: 48. Only fair: 27. Poor: 6. DK-NA: 6.
   12. Do you think George Bush will ask Congress to increase taxes
in the next four years? Yes: 71. No: 22. DK-NA: 8.
   13. Do you think George Bush should ask Congress to increase
taxes in the next four years? Yes: 32. No: 61. DK-NA: 7.
</TEXT>
