<UNK>Zsa Zsa Gabor Sues Delta For $10 Million Over Dogs Incident</UNK>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Zsa Zsa Gabor has filed a lawsuit against Delta
Air Lines over a Jan. 6 incident in which she was escorted off a
flight for refusing to cage her two dogs.
   ``They started it, this is just the kickoff,'' said Ms. Gabor's
attorney, Bernard Cohen of Hollywood, Fla. ``She's not going to
retreat. She's on the offensive.''
