<HEAD>Zambian Court Fines American, Canadian for Violating Airspace</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American and a Canadian pleaded guilty
Thursday to violating Zambian airspace in their small plane, and a
magistrate fined them $60 each.
   James Bruce Baker, 59, of Larksper, Colo., who was the pilot, and
Michael Quinn Bannock, 35, of Toronto, paid the fines after
admitting their plane flew into restricted airspace of the African
country on Saturday.
   According to their flight plan, they were traveling from the
United States to Mozambique with stops in Canada, Zaire, and
Zimbabwe.
