<HEAD>Bishops' Meeting on Priesthood Set For 1990</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A worldwide meeting of Roman Catholic bishops
on the priesthood will be held Sept. 30-Oct. 28, 1990, the Vatican
announced Thursday.
   The gathering of bishops is called a synod and is held every
three years to discuss various issues and problems in the church.
The last one was in October 1987 on the role of lay people in the
church.
