<HEAD>With AM-Hostages</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The head of the militia that guarded
hostage negotiator Terry Waite before he was kidnapped appealed on
Thursday for the release of the Anglican Church envoy.
   Walid Jumblatt called for Waite's release during an interview
broadcast by Lebanon's state television on the first anniversary of
Waite's capture.
   ``I do not think that Terry Waite is that big a spy. We should
emerge from this whirlpool (of hostage taking),'' he said without
