Anglican Church emissary before he vanished Jan. 20, 1987.
   The Druse militia leader has accused the Iranian-backed
Hezbollah, or Party of God, of holding Waite but the Shiite
fundamentalist group has denied it. No group has claimed
responsibility.
   Waite, 49, was on his fifth mission to Beirut to seek the release
of foreign hostages. He was last spotted after leaving a hotel in
Moslem west Beirut to meet with Shiite kidnappers.
   He had told his Druse bodyguards he did not want them to escort
him to the clandestine meeting, whose site he did not disclose.
   Fifteen Western foreigners are missing in Lebanon, including nine
Americans, most of them believed held by Shiites loyal to Iran.
   Longest held is Terry A. Anderson, 41, chief Middle East
correspondent of The Associated Press. He was kidnapped March 16,
1985.
