a list compiled by an automobile valuation service in Chicago.
   Thieves picked GM cars as their 22 most-popular targets,
according to the list released Wednesday by CCC Information Services
Inc., a business used by insurance companies to determine the value
of a stolen car.
   The 1986 Chevrolet Camaro topped the CCC list of stolen cars for
the second consecutive year. This year's list, based on 1988 car
thefts, has the '87 Camaro as No. 2; the '84 Camaro following that,
and the '85 Camaro as No. 4.
