<HEAD>December Rate Lowest Since February 1981</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unemployment in Britain fell to a seasonally
adjusted 7.2 percent of the workforce in December from 7.5 percent
in November, the government said Thursday.
   The December figure was the lowest since February 1981, the
Department of Employment said.
   The figure was down from 9.1 percent in December 1987.
   Total British unemployment was estimated at a seasonally adjusted
2.04 million people in December, down from a revised 2.11 million
people in November and 2.57 million people in December 1987.
   The monthly fall of 66,100 in the jobless total is the largest
monthly fall on record, the department said.
</TEXT>
