<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
244,098 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
231,175, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 211,315 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 152,440 cars this week,
compared with 145,403 a week ago and 127,773 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 91,658,
compared with last week's 85,772 and last year's 83,542.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,813 cars this week, up from
18,866 a week ago and from last year's 19,445.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,672, compared
with 19,496 a week ago and 19,595 in the same week last year.
