<FILEID>AP-NR-01-19-89 2258EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-Gerber     01-19 0179</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Gerber,0259</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gerber Reports Earnings Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREMONT, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gerber Products Co. said Thursday that its
fiscal third-quarter profit nearly doubled on rising baby food sales.
   Net income for the three months ended Dec. 31 totaled $19.1
million, or 96 cents a share, up from $9.7 million, or 49 cents a
share, a year ago. Quarterly sales rose to $240.1 million from
$227.1 million.
   For the first nine months of the fiscal year, Gerber netted $59.5
million, or $3.01 a share, on sales of $757.6 million. That compared
with earnings of $24.4 million, or $1.24 a share, and sales of
$683.7 million in the year-earlier period.
   The company said earnings would have been higher had it not been
for $2.5 million in losses from a baby furniture operation it sold
in December.
   Losses from discontinued operations cut earnings by $12.9 million
in the 1987 nine-month period.
   Besides a strong showing in baby food sales, income also
increased in Gerber's apparel group, which sells items under the
Gerber, Curity, Buster Brown and Weather Tamer brands, the company
said.
</TEXT>
