<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-PPG     01-19 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-PPG,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>PPG Profits Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   PPG Industries Inc. on Thursday reported a 6
percent increase in its fourt-quarter profit and a 24 percent jump
in earnings for all of 1988.
   Net income for the three months ended Dec. 31 totaled $102.3
million, or 94 cents a share, on sales of $1.4 billion. That
compared with earnings of $96.5 million, or 85 cents a share, and
sales of $1.3 billion a year ago.
   For the year, the company netted $467.6 million, or $4.26 a
share, on sales of $5.6 billion. In 1987, PPG's profit totaled
$377.1 million, or $3.19 a share, on $5.2 billion in sales.
   Chairman Vincent A. Sarni said gains were made in the company's
glass, coatings and chemicals division, its major businesses.
   ``For 1989 we expect to improve on our 1988 earnings
performance,'' Sarni said.
</TEXT>
